WEBVTT

00:01.060 --> 00:09.900
Subtitles by Synchronized

00:46.340 --> 00:50.875
the Year of our Lord
*1348*

00:53.971 --> 00:55.530
<i>The fumes of the dead,</i>

00:55.739 --> 00:57.739
<i>hung in the air like poison.</i>

00:59.051 --> 01:00.290
<i>A plague,</i>

01:00.493 --> 01:02.990
<i>more cruel and more
pitiless than war,</i>

01:03.256 --> 01:04.756
<i>had descended upon us.</i>

01:06.170 --> 01:07.260
<i>A pestilence,</i>

01:07.359 --> 01:09.859
<i>that would leave half
our kingdom dead.</i>

01:14.885 --> 01:16.385
<i>Where did it come from?</i>

01:17.301 --> 01:19.101
<i>What carried it's germ?</i>

01:21.011 --> 01:23.500
<i>The priests told us
it was God's punishment.</i>

01:24.522 --> 01:25.722
<i>For what sin?</i>

01:26.287 --> 01:29.130
<i>What commandment must we
break that would earn this?</i>

01:31.051 --> 01:32.051
<i>No.</i>

01:32.583 --> 01:33.920
<i>We knew the truth.</i>

01:35.651 --> 01:37.420
<i>This was not God's work,</i>

01:38.227 --> 01:39.427
<i>but devilry.</i>

01:40.510 --> 01:41.910
<i>Or witchcraft.</i>

01:42.889 --> 01:44.140
<i>And our task,</i>

01:44.444 --> 01:45.860
<i>to hunt down a demon,</i>

01:46.980 --> 01:48.338
<i>is God's cure.</i>

02:34.885 --> 02:35.985
Brother Thomas!

02:38.281 --> 02:39.481
Brother Thomas!

03:03.494 --> 03:04.790
Who was taken from us?

03:04.910 --> 03:06.211
Brother Ignatius.

03:06.423 --> 03:07.720
Is it the pestilence?

03:07.720 --> 03:09.054
We have not been told.

03:09.573 --> 03:10.873
I have no signs.

03:12.075 --> 03:13.260
Please brother.

03:14.842 --> 03:15.985
Let me out.

05:43.053 --> 05:44.053
Averill.

05:48.678 --> 05:50.178
O thanks pretty gorgeous.

05:50.636 --> 05:51.866
Where've you been?

05:51.985 --> 05:54.060
I was confined.
They thought I was sick.

06:01.460 --> 06:03.021
I thought you were dead.

06:03.428 --> 06:06.528
I'm alright.
I prayed, prayed all the time.

06:07.157 --> 06:08.257
I'm alright.

06:10.615 --> 06:11.815
I've brought food.

06:17.670 --> 06:18.861
One of our brothers,

06:19.590 --> 06:21.300
he died this morning, Averill.

06:21.760 --> 06:24.517
Even the monastery is no longer safe,
you must go now.

06:24.970 --> 06:29.040
You must go back to Dentwich Forest
and you must hide there till this is passed.

06:29.511 --> 06:30.700
On Sunday,

06:30.797 --> 06:32.106
the prior said the pestilence,

06:32.130 --> 06:34.908
was God's new purge
send to wash away our sins.

06:37.520 --> 06:38.800
Is God punishing us?

06:38.897 --> 06:39.897
No.

06:40.440 --> 06:41.440
No.

06:45.532 --> 06:46.732
You must go now.

06:48.084 --> 06:49.730
You must go back to Dentwich.

06:55.824 --> 06:56.920
You must go.

07:14.886 --> 07:16.021
Osmund, I...

07:16.323 --> 07:17.523
Averill, you'll die.

07:17.761 --> 07:19.061
And you will not?

07:24.974 --> 07:26.110
Come with me.

07:26.950 --> 07:28.588
If I leave the monastery now,

07:28.672 --> 07:29.772
I betray God.

07:30.928 --> 07:32.728
We've already betrayed him.

08:14.803 --> 08:16.206
You know the Martyrs Cross,

08:17.100 --> 08:18.272
at Dentwich forest?

08:20.456 --> 08:23.560
I will wait for you there,
every morning at dawn for one week.

08:27.110 --> 08:28.530
And then I will be gone.

09:05.950 --> 09:07.184
Forgive me, Father.

09:07.186 --> 09:08.386
I am confused.

09:08.672 --> 09:10.320
I confess, I am torn.

09:13.938 --> 09:16.370
Can I serve you outside of these walls?

09:16.889 --> 09:18.180
I would leave here,

09:18.290 --> 09:20.738
but I would never stray
from your grace, father.

09:23.529 --> 09:25.090
Show me Your will.

09:27.687 --> 09:29.100
Father, give me a sign.

10:05.650 --> 10:08.137
I am Ulric, envoy to the bishop.

10:09.628 --> 10:12.130
What I say know does
not leave these walls.

10:14.179 --> 10:17.779
Word has reached the bishop of a
village that does not suffer as the rest.

10:19.797 --> 10:22.160
They say it is a sanctuary
from the pestilence.

10:23.661 --> 10:28.100
There are many villages that have not
been ravaged yet by the pestilence.

10:28.179 --> 10:32.079
It is claimed, these villagers
are beyond death's icy grasp.

10:32.300 --> 10:33.937
Then they are gravely mistaken.

10:38.343 --> 10:40.200
These are difficult times.

10:41.679 --> 10:42.770
Such claims,

10:43.528 --> 10:44.928
however fantastical,

10:45.179 --> 10:48.579
can find favor with those less
educated than you or I.

10:49.804 --> 10:54.462
Precisely why we cannot fall
foul of rumor and superstition.

10:54.640 --> 10:56.979
God's grip on his people is lucent.

10:57.482 --> 11:01.948
We must ensure the flock is not tempted
to look beyond God and church for answers.

11:04.929 --> 11:07.729
I must see for myself how
this village is kept safe.

11:08.350 --> 11:10.230
What part have we in this?

11:10.324 --> 11:12.680
The village I seek lies in
the great marsh.

11:13.221 --> 11:14.786
I require a guide,

11:14.870 --> 11:16.880
a man of God to show the way.

11:17.138 --> 11:19.338
No man here fit for such a task.

11:21.846 --> 11:24.846
With the bishop's blessing
I may choose any man here.

11:25.769 --> 11:27.040
Out of respect,

11:27.930 --> 11:29.402
I grant you that choice.

11:29.513 --> 11:30.713
I will lead you there.

11:31.934 --> 11:34.210
No, he is a mere novice.

11:34.620 --> 11:36.837
This requires a more experienced hand.

11:36.920 --> 11:38.110
Let him speak.

11:38.638 --> 11:40.646
The said village you seek lies
in the great marsh.

11:40.734 --> 11:43.540
I was raised,
close by in Dentwich Forest.

11:44.169 --> 11:45.924
I know the area better than any man.

11:48.489 --> 11:50.338
He has all the experience I require.

11:52.070 --> 11:53.190
You will lead us.

11:53.312 --> 11:54.440
We leave at dawn.

11:56.930 --> 11:58.120
Osmund,

11:58.329 --> 12:01.529
that man is more dangerous
than the pestilence itself.

12:01.880 --> 12:03.411
Father, I prayed for guidance.

12:04.596 --> 12:05.696
God has answered.

12:25.805 --> 12:27.269
Even if you survive,

12:27.380 --> 12:29.271
the world out there will change you.

12:29.689 --> 12:31.378
Perhaps that's what I want Father.

13:54.180 --> 13:56.070
♪ My lady love and I ♪

13:56.163 --> 13:57.763
♪ We lived in joyeous sin ♪

13:58.130 --> 13:59.674
♪ Now my lady love ♪

13:59.760 --> 14:01.680
♪ Has got the blackened skin ♪

14:01.800 --> 14:03.256
♪ My lady love and I ♪

14:03.342 --> 14:05.242
♪ We pour our love so brave ♪

14:05.510 --> 14:06.776
♪ Now my lady love ♪

14:06.960 --> 14:08.790
♪ Rots in an early grave ♪

14:21.639 --> 14:22.739
We have our guide.

14:35.847 --> 14:37.347
God has no men left,

14:38.805 --> 14:40.205
he sends us a boy.

14:41.800 --> 14:43.104
Are you up to it, son?

14:43.388 --> 14:44.650
I can lead you there.

14:45.910 --> 14:46.980
Pray you do.

14:49.514 --> 14:51.714
Split any man from
his asshole to his apple.

14:52.597 --> 14:53.697
What's that for?

14:55.639 --> 14:56.939
How much does he know?

14:57.472 --> 14:58.617
Ulric was...

14:58.919 --> 15:00.441
frugal shall we say,

15:01.443 --> 15:02.443
with the truth.

15:04.972 --> 15:06.472
This village we're headed to...

15:07.783 --> 15:09.270
they've cast God aside.

15:09.680 --> 15:11.270
In his place sits a demon.

15:12.672 --> 15:14.160
There was talk of sacrifice.

15:14.696 --> 15:16.250
Of men eating men,

15:16.682 --> 15:18.050
and of raising the dead.

15:18.451 --> 15:19.560
Now we're charged,

15:19.741 --> 15:21.940
to bring the leader of this village
back for confession,

15:21.970 --> 15:23.270
trial and execution.

15:23.720 --> 15:26.362
The bishop seeks to roast
themself a necromancer.

15:26.479 --> 15:27.830
Sorry, what is a necromancer?

15:27.971 --> 15:29.110
A necromancer,

15:29.355 --> 15:31.020
is someone who plucks the dead,

15:31.120 --> 15:32.160
from the cold earth,

15:32.639 --> 15:34.439
breathes new life into them.

15:36.347 --> 15:37.400
We have the tools,

15:37.623 --> 15:38.700
we have the will.

15:39.056 --> 15:40.356
We journey into hell.

15:42.264 --> 15:43.601
But God travels with us.

15:43.900 --> 15:45.021
So you misled me.

15:46.056 --> 15:48.238
Return to your monastery
if you feel betrayed,

15:48.240 --> 15:49.240
or join us...

15:49.612 --> 15:51.012
and do God's work.

15:51.789 --> 15:54.489
Let's get this cleared up,
let's get going!

15:56.155 --> 15:57.930
That includes you, Swire.

16:42.723 --> 16:44.323
We are not as bad as you think.

16:45.889 --> 16:49.753
We're worse.
But we need you alive.

16:50.400 --> 16:52.700
You seem well suited
to keeping men alive.

16:54.181 --> 16:57.981
I've spent many a long years in
the king's army with Wolfstan and Griff.

16:58.550 --> 16:59.835
I'll be honest with ya.

17:00.005 --> 17:01.840
We've never faced a demon before,

17:02.160 --> 17:03.708
but we take what comes our way.

17:04.436 --> 17:05.640
What happened to him?

17:05.910 --> 17:07.150
Ivo was captured.

17:07.973 --> 17:09.276
Wouldn't talk,

17:09.578 --> 17:11.877
so the bastard French tore out
his tongue.

17:15.390 --> 17:16.207
And him?

17:16.271 --> 17:17.972
Mold is a men to leave alone...

17:18.306 --> 17:20.006
unless there is butchery to be done.

17:20.306 --> 17:21.357
And Dalywag,

17:21.825 --> 17:23.020
he is a torturer,

17:23.185 --> 17:24.220
a hangman,

17:24.464 --> 17:25.829
and if the rumor is true,

17:25.920 --> 17:26.829
murderer,

17:26.901 --> 17:28.901
thief and defiler of women.

17:29.595 --> 17:31.280
But apart from that,
he's a good man.

17:33.007 --> 17:34.160
What about Ulric?

17:34.362 --> 17:35.860
I've got a wife and child.

17:36.235 --> 17:37.524
I'm here for the money.

17:37.630 --> 17:39.126
Ulric is here because,

17:39.515 --> 17:41.520
God told him to come.

17:44.129 --> 17:45.129
Burn!

17:53.473 --> 17:54.473
Burn!

17:55.515 --> 17:58.217
Have mercy, please have mercy.

18:04.681 --> 18:05.781
I've done nothing.

18:07.550 --> 18:09.355
- We must help her.
- Do you hear me?

18:09.442 --> 18:10.799
You deserve to burn!

18:10.890 --> 18:12.126
I've done nothing.
Burn!

18:12.128 --> 18:14.405
Burn the witch! Burn!

18:18.470 --> 18:20.047
You're in league with the devil.

18:20.050 --> 18:21.042
What is her crime?

18:21.437 --> 18:23.058
She brought death to our village.

18:23.535 --> 18:25.500
Death is all around us,
and it's no invitation.

18:25.515 --> 18:27.508
This does not involve you monk,
step aside.

18:27.710 --> 18:29.626
I have done nothing, please.

18:29.741 --> 18:31.140
Please, stand aside.

18:35.515 --> 18:37.013
What is this woman accused of?

18:37.038 --> 18:40.046
She poisoned our well in a pact with
the devil now half the village is dead.

18:40.070 --> 18:42.338
I offered a simple blessing
over our water,

18:42.489 --> 18:43.610
to keep everyone safe.

18:43.765 --> 18:44.236
Liar.

18:44.238 --> 18:45.338
I did nothing wrong.

18:45.339 --> 18:45.931
Liar!

18:45.932 --> 18:47.770
The dying began after
she was seen at the well.

18:47.772 --> 18:48.772
You have her confession?

18:48.773 --> 18:50.490
Plenty of us saw her cast her spell.

18:50.492 --> 18:51.593
Now she must burn,

18:51.703 --> 18:53.703
to spare what remains of our village.

18:56.456 --> 18:57.610
Move aside.

19:04.037 --> 19:05.570
I will not ask you again.

19:05.848 --> 19:06.848
Back.

19:27.099 --> 19:28.199
Thank you.

19:51.140 --> 19:52.440
Do not stop again.

19:55.490 --> 19:57.290
Come on, brown slug.

20:03.432 --> 20:05.860
As sure as the sun will rise and fall,

20:06.000 --> 20:08.160
witches will burn.

20:08.932 --> 20:13.932
There's a village in the north,
that burned 128 witches in one night.

20:14.437 --> 20:17.580
That's sixteen an hour, for eight hours.

20:17.807 --> 20:19.691
By the time that night was through,

20:19.811 --> 20:21.890
they'd killed every woman in the village.

20:22.557 --> 20:25.157
By the end of that week
the men were shagging pigs.

20:25.932 --> 20:27.729
Pestilence isn't trial enough,

20:28.362 --> 20:30.030
now God has us shagging pigs.

20:32.432 --> 20:33.889
This village we seek,

20:34.541 --> 20:35.543
you been there?

20:35.844 --> 20:36.890
No.

20:37.768 --> 20:39.168
But I know where it lies.

20:39.599 --> 20:40.938
Hell awaits us,

20:41.294 --> 20:42.334
or so we're told.

20:42.432 --> 20:45.110
If you've not got the stomach for it,
then leave it now.

20:45.509 --> 20:47.509
And I'll have your share
of the bounty.

20:48.391 --> 20:51.391
What is the Church believe
this pestilence is come from?

20:51.974 --> 20:54.674
I don't believe God is punishing us
like many do.

20:55.529 --> 20:56.950
I say from France,

20:57.756 --> 20:59.656
where all foul things emerge.

21:00.849 --> 21:03.449
For once Swire, you might
not be too far from the truth.

21:05.557 --> 21:08.857
Three summers passed we fought
a battle at Crecy, in Normandy,

21:09.628 --> 21:11.440
King Edward's army was dwarfed.

21:12.428 --> 21:15.487
For every twenty of us, there were
a hundred Frenchmen, at least.

21:16.266 --> 21:17.266
The French...

21:18.266 --> 21:19.466
Ah, the French.

21:20.823 --> 21:22.290
They could sense victory,

21:22.696 --> 21:23.796
you could smell it.

21:25.300 --> 21:27.027
On that day for the first time,

21:27.600 --> 21:29.320
our archers used the longbow.

21:30.141 --> 21:32.541
Quicker to load, further in flight.

21:33.090 --> 21:34.117
Their arrows,

21:34.230 --> 21:35.530
their arrows were useless.

21:35.647 --> 21:36.752
Couldn't reach us.

21:37.505 --> 21:38.616
And ours,

21:39.002 --> 21:40.540
ours were like a dark,

21:40.663 --> 21:41.640
buzzing cloud.

21:42.461 --> 21:43.640
And that day's end,

21:44.404 --> 21:47.540
field was littered with their dead
and their dying.

21:48.809 --> 21:49.800
And custom,

21:49.952 --> 21:51.440
how matter how fierce the battle,

21:51.849 --> 21:53.649
was to use the misericorde.

21:53.769 --> 21:55.780
Misericorde, it's the 'mercy-giver'.

21:57.308 --> 22:00.110
You stab straight through
the armpit directly into the heart,

22:00.202 --> 22:01.482
it's quick and painless.

22:01.958 --> 22:02.958
But on this day,

22:03.491 --> 22:04.991
there was an end to chivalry.

22:05.641 --> 22:08.490
King Edward ordered
every Frenchman left alive,

22:08.580 --> 22:10.575
to be killed without mercy.

22:12.433 --> 22:13.433
Arms,

22:13.981 --> 22:15.041
heads,

22:15.425 --> 22:16.520
legs,

22:16.790 --> 22:17.810
hacked away.

22:19.130 --> 22:20.582
God's greatest army,

22:21.435 --> 22:22.978
descended into savagery.

22:27.266 --> 22:28.364
Forgive me,

22:28.660 --> 22:30.752
but how does that conscern
the pestilence?

22:31.223 --> 22:33.000
We invited death among us that day.

22:34.602 --> 22:36.197
He hasn't left us since.

23:08.558 --> 23:09.858
That woman you killed,

23:11.567 --> 23:13.054
she was not a witch.

23:16.641 --> 23:18.541
Why did you volanteer to join us, monk?

23:20.975 --> 23:22.175
To serve God.

23:23.689 --> 23:25.204
Killing witches serves God.

23:27.558 --> 23:29.258
The woman was already dead.

23:31.183 --> 23:32.443
If I had freed her,

23:32.740 --> 23:35.392
the mob would have caught
her again and burned her.

23:37.558 --> 23:39.058
I spared her suffering.

23:42.970 --> 23:44.666
Sometimes that is all you can do.

25:12.100 --> 25:13.400
He says turn back.

25:15.059 --> 25:16.332
Where we're headed,

25:17.044 --> 25:18.480
men have become savages.

25:50.809 --> 25:53.750
It must've been something
pretty special to tempt you away

25:53.769 --> 25:55.869
from that nice warm monastery.

26:02.390 --> 26:03.825
Anything you wanna tell me?

26:04.038 --> 26:05.038
No.

26:11.976 --> 26:13.276
You know what my job is?

26:15.270 --> 26:16.456
I am a torturer,

26:17.369 --> 26:18.489
truth-getter.

26:19.025 --> 26:20.440
Spend hours on a man.

26:20.705 --> 26:22.147
Can smell a lie,

26:22.849 --> 26:24.249
and I smell you.

26:25.152 --> 26:27.020
Pray somewhere else,
if I were you.

27:12.900 --> 27:15.000
Have you broken any vows yet, boy?

27:16.100 --> 27:17.300
Leave him be, Mold.

27:22.559 --> 27:24.189
Back, get back!

27:24.491 --> 27:25.491
Griff!

27:26.434 --> 27:27.434
Griff?

27:32.393 --> 27:34.710
- I said get back!
- Leave me alone.

27:34.893 --> 27:35.893
Let me look.

27:38.941 --> 27:39.910
Let me look.

27:42.720 --> 27:44.202
Just going to take a look.

27:45.893 --> 27:46.893
Alright?

27:47.557 --> 27:48.650
Ok my friend.

27:48.960 --> 27:50.136
Just having a look.

28:26.101 --> 28:27.501
Why didn't you tell us?

28:29.660 --> 28:30.643
I'm sorry.

28:32.101 --> 28:33.601
His journey is finished here.

28:42.226 --> 28:43.426
I prefer mercy.

28:47.143 --> 28:48.937
I need to make a confession to the friar.

28:49.068 --> 28:50.230
No.

28:50.310 --> 28:52.110
Cannot be sure how this thing spread.

28:52.111 --> 28:54.311
Who the hell asked you?

28:58.351 --> 28:59.751
I will take your confession.

29:02.185 --> 29:03.585
Come, you shall have absolution.

29:10.727 --> 29:13.557
You keep your mouth, shut!

29:24.014 --> 29:26.330
Ego te absolvo a peccatis tuis,

29:26.735 --> 29:29.346
in nomine Patris et Filii et Spiritus Sancti.

29:29.520 --> 29:30.521
Forgive me.

29:36.062 --> 29:37.647
Our Father which art in heaven.

29:38.643 --> 29:39.843
Halowed by thy name.

29:40.977 --> 29:42.077
Let thy kingdom come.

29:43.181 --> 29:45.510
Thy will be fulfilled as well
in heven as it is earth.

29:46.644 --> 29:48.340
Give this daily bred give today.

29:54.560 --> 29:55.760
I need a moment with him.

29:57.310 --> 29:58.310
Alright.

30:14.906 --> 30:15.940
I'm glad it's you.

30:17.542 --> 30:18.542
I can see things...

30:30.477 --> 30:31.777
Farewell my friend.

30:47.369 --> 30:48.367
Bury him.

31:22.936 --> 31:24.212
The forest of Dentwich.

31:24.856 --> 31:26.210
How far to the marsh?

31:26.880 --> 31:28.271
Half a day, perhaps less.

31:29.144 --> 31:30.315
Be on your guard.

31:31.204 --> 31:33.340
God has slipped over the horizon.

31:45.686 --> 31:47.186
You're on watch tonight, Swire.

32:00.144 --> 32:01.744
Giving Griff absolution...

32:03.644 --> 32:04.744
took courage.

32:13.852 --> 32:16.452
Do you truly believe this
village can rise the dead?

32:18.140 --> 32:19.840
I would not be here otherwise.

32:21.373 --> 32:22.473
You doubt it?

32:24.394 --> 32:28.064
I believe that hunting necromancers
and demons serves men,

32:28.104 --> 32:29.304
more than it serves god.

32:31.769 --> 32:34.769
You have learned much
nestled inside the monastery.

32:38.478 --> 32:40.978
Demons and necromancers
are among us.

32:43.600 --> 32:44.900
As you will find out.

32:46.670 --> 32:47.870
Soon enough.

32:51.994 --> 32:53.394
I'll get some sleep.

33:55.728 --> 33:56.828
Averill?

34:02.020 --> 34:03.020
Averill?

34:09.478 --> 34:10.578
Averill?

