01:14:31.783 --> 01:14:33.030
We have no pestilence.

01:14:33.040 --> 01:14:34.370
We have no God.

01:14:35.280 --> 01:14:37.054
Why are you doing this to me?

01:14:38.456 --> 01:14:39.630
Because I like you.

01:14:45.574 --> 01:14:47.474
Renounce and you will be together.

01:14:49.660 --> 01:14:50.654
Go.

01:14:51.929 --> 01:14:52.940
Go.

01:14:57.241 --> 01:14:58.241
Osmund.

01:14:58.332 --> 01:14:59.332
Osmund.

01:14:59.907 --> 01:15:01.207
Do not be tempted.

01:15:02.028 --> 01:15:03.270
It is not her.

01:15:03.487 --> 01:15:04.850
It is not her!

01:15:06.830 --> 01:15:07.866
Osmund!

01:15:08.447 --> 01:15:09.530
Osmund!

01:16:16.866 --> 01:16:17.866
Averill.

01:16:23.449 --> 01:16:24.749
No, come here.

01:16:27.158 --> 01:16:28.298
No, Averill.

01:16:44.574 --> 01:16:46.233
Averill, look at me.

01:16:56.408 --> 01:16:57.408
It is alright.

01:16:58.533 --> 01:16:59.633
It's alright.

01:17:00.533 --> 01:17:01.733
You're with God.

01:17:02.699 --> 01:17:03.899
You're with God.

01:17:06.158 --> 01:17:08.312
And very soon, I'll be with you.

01:17:08.314 --> 01:17:09.514
I promise you.

01:17:10.533 --> 01:17:11.733
I promise.

01:17:27.450 --> 01:17:29.050
I love you, Averill.

01:17:32.866 --> 01:17:34.166
In nomine Patris...

01:17:35.241 --> 01:17:36.241
et Filii...

01:17:37.533 --> 01:17:39.195
et Spiritus Sancti.

01:17:39.197 --> 01:17:40.197
Amen.

01:19:01.950 --> 01:19:03.250
Averill is with God.

01:19:06.242 --> 01:19:07.742
And so am I.

01:19:11.908 --> 01:19:13.908
This shows how cruel they are.

01:19:14.617 --> 01:19:17.717
Even the ones they love are
slaughtered in God's name.

01:19:27.617 --> 01:19:29.417
The boy will not renounce.

01:19:29.718 --> 01:19:31.418
The boy will not renounce.

01:19:32.200 --> 01:19:33.876
You have no power here.

01:19:34.278 --> 01:19:35.978
You have no power here.

01:19:37.659 --> 01:19:38.659
Hob,

01:19:39.317 --> 01:19:40.517
crucify them all.

01:19:40.575 --> 01:19:42.900
You can not tear a true man of God,

01:19:42.902 --> 01:19:44.402
away from his faith.

01:19:45.492 --> 01:19:47.230
I do not fear you,

01:19:47.632 --> 01:19:49.132
nor your pagan lapdog.

01:19:51.075 --> 01:19:52.075
Finished?

01:19:54.367 --> 01:19:55.667
Bring out the horses.

01:20:07.575 --> 01:20:08.935
Crucify us,

01:20:09.337 --> 01:20:11.137
and you shall be spared.

01:20:13.159 --> 01:20:15.239
That is the creed of your witch.

01:20:15.659 --> 01:20:18.259
You came to our land bringing death.

01:20:18.784 --> 01:20:20.384
For once you speak the truth.

01:20:21.659 --> 01:20:23.259
We came bringing death.

01:20:24.576 --> 01:20:26.276
She cannot protect you,

01:20:26.428 --> 01:20:27.828
from God's wrath.

01:20:29.159 --> 01:20:30.161
Repent!

01:20:30.463 --> 01:20:31.963
Before it is too late.

01:20:32.951 --> 01:20:33.951
Hit it.

01:20:34.826 --> 01:20:35.926
Repent!

01:20:52.201 --> 01:20:53.401
You will renounce.

01:20:55.326 --> 01:20:56.326
Never.

01:21:01.409 --> 01:21:03.509
No! No!

01:21:08.201 --> 01:21:09.201
Never.

01:21:36.534 --> 01:21:37.534
Stop!

01:21:51.284 --> 01:21:52.484
Let me see the boy.

01:22:14.951 --> 01:22:16.051
You did well.

01:22:20.368 --> 01:22:22.280
Come on, come on, come.

01:22:25.659 --> 01:22:27.359
They will all die by God's hand.

01:22:32.034 --> 01:22:33.334
Open my shirt.

01:22:39.118 --> 01:22:40.418
Open my shirt.

01:22:58.576 --> 01:22:59.676
I am Death.

01:23:02.035 --> 01:23:03.435
Vengeance is mine.

01:23:06.576 --> 01:23:09.776
God's fury rains down on you.

01:23:11.243 --> 01:23:12.643
God is restored.

01:23:19.360 --> 01:23:20.360
Run.

01:24:05.152 --> 01:24:06.452
Where are you?

01:25:56.052 --> 01:25:57.952
Hell awaits you with open arms.

01:25:58.233 --> 01:25:59.733
There is no hell.

01:26:00.077 --> 01:26:01.554
Well, heaven doesn't want you.

01:26:01.556 --> 01:26:03.456
There is no heaven.

01:26:03.764 --> 01:26:04.820
Why?

01:26:05.080 --> 01:26:06.280
Why follow her?

01:26:07.494 --> 01:26:09.094
Because she was beautiful.

01:26:11.244 --> 01:26:12.444
And real.

01:26:13.490 --> 01:26:14.607
This...

01:26:15.869 --> 01:26:17.069
is real.

01:26:26.994 --> 01:26:31.594
There is no God.

01:26:37.161 --> 01:26:38.161
Where are you?

01:26:51.952 --> 01:26:53.152
Where are you?

01:26:55.544 --> 01:26:57.914
Thou shalt not kill.

01:26:58.328 --> 01:26:59.328
Remember?

01:27:01.661 --> 01:27:02.661
Remember?

01:27:03.578 --> 01:27:05.578
Averill was in purgatory.

01:27:06.411 --> 01:27:08.611
Perhaps in your twisted mind.

01:27:09.119 --> 01:27:11.819
Did you never think that
maybe Averill was never dead?

01:27:14.953 --> 01:27:16.652
We found her in the forrest,

01:27:16.654 --> 01:27:18.817
injured but very much alive.

01:27:19.036 --> 01:27:20.536
You know that is not true.

01:27:21.119 --> 01:27:22.275
Yes Osmund,

01:27:22.277 --> 01:27:25.277
Averill was never dead.
She was alive.

01:27:26.911 --> 01:27:28.511
I drugged her.

01:27:29.953 --> 01:27:31.453
I drugged her.

01:27:43.994 --> 01:27:44.994
So why...

01:27:45.578 --> 01:27:47.228
Why w...
Why would you do that?

01:27:47.230 --> 01:27:48.430
Why would you bury her?

01:27:48.744 --> 01:27:50.944
Because people need miracles.

01:27:51.494 --> 01:27:54.994
And they worship the miracle makers,
whoever they might be.

01:27:59.786 --> 01:28:02.686
The people in this village
believed in me.

01:28:03.286 --> 01:28:04.734
And so did you.

01:28:04.736 --> 01:28:06.536
No, Averill was dead.

01:28:06.953 --> 01:28:08.353
You killed her.

01:28:11.120 --> 01:28:12.620
Averill was dead.

01:28:21.286 --> 01:28:22.386
She was dead.

01:28:29.328 --> 01:28:30.528
Bring her back.

01:28:33.411 --> 01:28:35.411
I beg you, bring her back.

01:28:37.453 --> 01:28:39.453
No, I can't.

01:28:40.578 --> 01:28:42.078
Pray to your God.

01:28:42.995 --> 01:28:44.395
See what he can do.

01:28:54.328 --> 01:28:55.628
She was dead.

01:29:22.328 --> 01:29:24.131
<i>There is nothing beautiful,</i>

01:29:24.133 --> 01:29:25.373
<i>or uplifting,</i>

01:29:25.375 --> 01:29:27.275
<i>in returning people to God.</i>

01:29:30.203 --> 01:29:32.703
<i>There is no place
in heaven for those who kill.</i>

01:29:36.287 --> 01:29:37.362
<i>The pestilence,</i>

01:29:37.564 --> 01:29:39.264
<i>claimed no higher purpose.</i>

01:29:40.203 --> 01:29:42.803
<i>And those who had survived
our swords that day.</i>

01:29:43.574 --> 01:29:45.674
<i>Soon fell foul of its sighs.</i>

01:29:47.953 --> 01:29:49.953
<i>They were not protected by the witch.</i>

01:29:51.453 --> 01:29:53.053
<i>They were simply remote.</i>

01:29:54.620 --> 01:29:57.120
<i>And once the pestilence
crossed their marsh.</i>

01:29:58.620 --> 01:30:00.020
<i>It killed them too.</i>

01:30:21.079 --> 01:30:22.079
Osmund.

01:30:23.912 --> 01:30:24.912
Osmund.

01:30:27.745 --> 01:30:28.845
We're here.

01:30:43.620 --> 01:30:44.620
Osmund.

01:30:48.995 --> 01:30:51.395
That you've returned safe
is a miracle.

01:30:54.370 --> 01:30:55.416
Who is that?

01:30:55.718 --> 01:30:58.518
It's a necromancer that
I'll be delivering to the bishop.

01:31:00.995 --> 01:31:01.995
Here,

01:31:02.572 --> 01:31:03.572
that's it...

01:31:13.120 --> 01:31:14.420
How many of you are left.

01:31:15.120 --> 01:31:16.220
Enough.

01:31:18.662 --> 01:31:19.862
Look after him.

01:31:21.537 --> 01:31:23.037
There's no need.

01:31:24.787 --> 01:31:26.287
He is back with God.

01:31:48.037 --> 01:31:49.437
<i>I never saw him again.</i>

01:31:51.162 --> 01:31:52.362
<i>I heard stories.</i>

01:31:54.329 --> 01:31:55.629
<i>Dark stories.</i>

01:31:57.371 --> 01:31:59.071
<i>That in the years that followed,</i>

01:32:00.076 --> 01:32:01.876
<i>Osmund's heart turned cold.</i>

01:32:03.037 --> 01:32:04.801
<i>That in the shadow of his grief,</i>

01:32:05.503 --> 01:32:07.103
<i>he found a hate.</i>

01:32:07.579 --> 01:32:08.879
<i>And that in God's name...</i>

01:32:09.537 --> 01:32:11.054
<i>he took up the sword</i>

01:32:11.556 --> 01:32:12.765
<i>and vengeance</i>

01:32:13.167 --> 01:32:14.467
<i>became his creed.</i>

01:32:20.996 --> 01:32:22.196
Can I help you?

01:32:40.663 --> 01:32:41.663
Please.

01:32:43.079 --> 01:32:44.079
Please.

01:32:47.163 --> 01:32:48.563
I've done nothing wrong.

01:32:51.663 --> 01:32:52.663
Please.

01:32:53.663 --> 01:32:54.663
Please.

01:32:57.621 --> 01:32:59.221
You have the wrong woman.

01:33:02.746 --> 01:33:04.946
I want a confession
and I want her alive.

01:33:14.347 --> 01:33:15.347
My God.

01:33:30.948 --> 01:33:31.948
Please...

01:33:49.705 --> 01:33:50.705
Osmund.

01:33:51.663 --> 01:33:52.863
She won't confess.

01:33:53.621 --> 01:33:55.021
Are you sure she's a witch?

01:34:02.538 --> 01:34:03.638
Where is she?

01:34:11.746 --> 01:34:13.646
<i>Some say he found the witch,</i>

01:34:13.915 --> 01:34:15.410
<i>and that he tortured her,</i>

01:34:15.585 --> 01:34:16.710
<i>and burned her.</i>

01:34:21.371 --> 01:34:22.518
<i>Others say,</i>

01:34:22.696 --> 01:34:24.020
<i>it was never her,</i>

01:34:27.068 --> 01:34:29.120
<i>it was only her guilt he saw,</i>

01:34:29.270 --> 01:34:30.980
<i>in the eyes of the accused.</i>

01:34:57.830 --> 01:34:59.780
<i>I like to think that he found peace,</i>

01:35:01.620 --> 01:35:04.004
<i>that he continued seeing
beauty in the world,</i>

01:35:05.755 --> 01:35:06.930
<i>goodness.</i>

01:35:09.840 --> 01:35:16.320
Subtitles by Synchronized
